'''Randy Gage''' (born April 6, 1959)<ref>{{cite web|title=Randy Gage - Famous Birthdays|url=http://www.famousbirthdays.com/people/randy-gage.html|publisher=Famous Birthdays|accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref> is an American author, entrepreneur, and professional speaker. 

==Background==

Born in Madison, Wisconsin, Gage is the son of Kay and Robert Gage, although he never met his father (now deceased).   Gage was a teenage alcoholic and drug addict and ran into early trouble with the law, ending up in juvenile detention for burglary and armed robbery. He was expelled from Madison West Senior High School.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tan|first1=Lorna|title=Ex-Delinquent, Now Millionaire|url=http://www.randygage.com/pdf/media/Ex_delinquent_now_millionaire_featuring_Randy_Gage.pdf|accessdate=November 21, 2014|publisher=The Straights Times|date=November 15, 2009}}</ref>

==Career==

Gage founded Prosperity Factory, Inc. in 1991 providing consulting and information products on success and prosperity<ref>{{cite web|title=Division of Corporations|url=http://search.sunbiz.org/Inquiry/CorporationSearch/SearchResultDetail?inquirytype=EntityName&directionType=Initial&searchNameOrder=PROSPERITYFACTORY%20S803721&aggregateId=domp-s80372-195a1e35-b704-4904-9fe7-de9a565bd369&searchTerm=prosperity%20factory&listNameOrder=PROSPERITYFACTORY%20S803721|website=Florida Department of State|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref>. Gage served as president of the Florida Speakers Association from 1996 to 1997<ref>{{cite web|title = Past Presidents - Florida Speakers Association|url=http://www.floridaspeakers.org/fsa-past-presidents/|publisher=Florida Speakers Association|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref> and was awarded their Award of Excellence (2003), Member of the Year (1996), and Lifetime Achievement Award (1999)<ref>{{cite web|title=Awards - Florida Speakers Association|url=http://www.floridaspeakers.org/about-fsa/award-winning-speaker-prior-to-2008/|publisher=Florida Speakers Association|accessdate=November 21, 2014}}</ref>. In 2013, Gage was inducted into the Speakers Hall of Fame by the National Speakers Association<ref>{{cite web|title=CPAE Speaker Hall of Fame|url=http://www.nsaspeaker.org/community/recognition/cpae-speaker-hall-of-fame/|publisher=National Speakers Association|accessdate=November 21, 2014}}</ref>. He was listed in the <U+201C>Who<U+2019>s Hot<U+201D> profile in SPEAKER magazine in 2009<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pettit|first1=Jessica|title=Who's Hot - 25 Men and Women Who Are Shaping Our Profession|url=http://www.kirklandproductions.com/marketing/Jessica_Pettitt_Article.pdf|publisher=National Speakers Association|accessdate=November 21, 2014}}</ref>. 

Gage is also an independent distributor for [[Agel Enterprises]], LLC., where he serves as head of their Advisory Board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Agel - Randy Gage|url=http://www.agel.com/randy-gage|publisher=Agel Enterprises, LLC|accessdate=November 20, 2014}}</ref>

==Writings==

Gage has authored nine books, which have been translated into 25 languages;  all except two of them have been published by his own company.  He is best known for ''Risky Is the New Safe,'' published by [[Wiley]],  which reached number 10 on the New York Times Best Seller list<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2012-11-18/hardcover-advice/list.html|publisher=New York Times|title=Best Seller List|accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref>, number 1 on the Wall Street Journal Best Seller list (non-fiction, Business)<ref>{{cite news|title=Wall Street Journal Best Seller List|url=http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424127887324439804578104841200997044?mod=WSJ_Books_LS_Books_13&mg=reno64-wsj&url=http%3A%2F%2Fonline.wsj.com%2Farticle%2FSB10001424127887324439804578104841200997044.html%3Fmod%3DWSJ_Books_LS_Books_13|accessdate=22 November 2014|publisher=Wall Street Journal}}</ref>, and was featured in [[USA Today]] as the number 1 money book.{{cn}}

===books published by third party publishers===
* Gage, Randy (2012). ''Risky is the New Safe: The Rules Have Changed''. John Wiley & Sons. ISBN 9781118481479. First published in English.<r  Translated into Turkish, Russian, Bulgarian, German, Korean, Czech, and Polish, {{cn}} ; most translations published by  Innsbruck Life Success Media 
* Gage, Randy (2006). ''Why You're Dumb, Sick and Broke...And How to Get Smart, Healthy and Rich!''. John Wiley & Sons. ISBN 9780470049310. 263 library holdings, according to WorldCat<ef>[http://www.worldcat.org/wcidentities/np-gage,%20randy WorldCat author listing </ref> First published in English. Translated into Polish, Spanish, Bahasa Indonesian, Czech,  Korean, Romanian/Moldavian, Portuguese, Bulgarian, and Chinese. {{cn}} 

===Books published by Prime Concepts Group===

* Gage, Randy (2011). ''Making the First Circle Work: The Foundation for Duplication in Network Marketing''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780967316451. First published in English. Translated to Hungarian, Russian, and German. 
* Gage, Randy (2003). ''Accept Your Abundance!. Prime Concepts Group''. ISBN 9780971557888. First published in English. Translated into Russian, Portuguese, Spanish, and German.
* Gage, Randy (2003). ''Prosperity Mind: How to Harness the Power of Thought''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780971557864. First published in English. Translated into Russian, Portuguese, Bahasa Indonesian, Spanish, Korean and German.
* Gage, Randy (2003). ''The 7 Spiritual Laws of Prosperity''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780971557857. First published in English. Translated into Bahasa Indonesian, Russian, Portuguese, Spanish, German, Romanian, and Korean. 
* Gage, Randy (2003). ''101 Keys to Your Prosperity''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780971557840. First published in English, Translated to Thai, Russian, Portuguese, Baha Indonesian, and German.
* Gage, Randy (2003). ''37 Secrets about Prosperity''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780971557871. First published in English. Translated into Russian, Portuguese, Baha Indonesian Romanian, and German.
* Gage, Randy (2001). ''How to Build a Multi-level Money Machine: The Science of Network Marketing''. Prime Concepts Group. ISBN 9780967316468. First published in English. Translated into Bulgarian, Hungarian, Russian, German, Bahasa Indonesian, Polish, and Czech.

